        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Lab Overview {.unnumbered}\n",
        "\n",
        "This lab transitions from **count-based representations** (Bag of Words, TF-IDF)\n",
        "to **learned semantic representations** (word embeddings) — the foundation of modern\n",
        "neural NLP and generative AI systems.\n",
        "\n",
        "| Representation | Core Idea | Limitation |\n",
        "|---|---|---|\n",
        "| Bag of Words | Count occurrences | Ignores meaning and order |\n",
        "| TF-IDF | Weight by rarity | Still no semantics |\n",
        "| Word Embeddings | Learn from context | Requires training data |\n",
        "| Transformer embeddings | Full context | Computationally expensive |\n",
        "\n",
        "Each row builds on the previous.\n",
        "This lab focuses on the **word embeddings** row.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "## Learning Objectives {.unnumbered}\n",
        "\n",
        "After completing this lab you should be able to:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Explain the distributional hypothesis and why it motivates embeddings.\n",
        "2. Build a `Vocabulary` class that maps tokens to integer indices.\n",
        "3. Implement a PyTorch `nn.Embedding` layer and inspect learned vectors.\n",
        "4. Compute cosine similarity between word vectors.\n",
        "5. Visualize word clusters using PCA.\n",
        "6. Articulate one business analytics use case for word embeddings.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "## Setup {.unnumbered}"
